    "ReviewDiscover Civil Engineering (2024) 1:145 | https://doi.org/10.1007/s44290-024-00154-z 4.2.11 SCBA Ganesan et al. [100] and Bahurudeen et al.",
    "[101] found that SCBA replacement levels up to 20% by weight increased compressive strength by 8-10% at 28 days, though flexural strength remained stable or decreased slightly.",
    "Similarly, Cordeiro et al. [102] and Murugesan et al.",
    "[106] reported improvements in both compressive and tensile strengths with 10-20% SCBA replacements, suggesting that moderate levels of SCBA are effective in enhancing concrete strength.",
    "Other studies, such as Singh et al. [103] and Jha et al."
